cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the design and analysis of a new variant of bit interleaved coded modulation (BICM) for communication systems. The paper focuses on the information theoretic aspects of the scheme, such as capacity, error exponent, and channel dispersion. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with communication systems and coding, which suggests that it could belong to cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a new finite-length interleaver, which could also place it in cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper uses analytical and numerical methods to evaluate the performance of the scheme, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
